{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4e742edb-1ea2-4f11-b2f5-2f31714cd459","content":"Here's what needs to change:\n\n1. **Remove** the old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. **Replace** `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` with the unified `MSTest` v3 package (it bundles the framework, adapter, and test SDK)\n\nYour test code (`[TestClass]`, `[TestMethod]`, namespace) is already compatible — no changes needed there.\n\nWant me to apply these changes to the `.csproj`?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d9de28e6-7186-431b-a9f6-855c1edd19ec","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has:\n\n1. A `.csproj` targeting `net462` with an old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. An old `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` version (17.5.0)\n3. Test code using `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting` namespace\n\nTo upgrade to MSTest v3:\n\n1. **Remove** the old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. **Replace** the `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` package with the unified `MSTest` package (v3+), or add `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages. Actually, MSTest v3 introduced a single `MSTest` meta-package.\n\n\n3. The target framework `net462` is already at the minimum supported version for MSTest v3, so no framework upgrade is needed. The unified `MSTest` package handles both the test framework and adapter, and the namespace stays the same for backward compatibility.\n\nFor the actual changes, I need to remove the old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework` and replace `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` with the single `MSTest` package at version 3.7.0 or later.\n\nThe test code itself should remain unchanged since MSTest v3 maintains backward compatibility with the existing `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting` namespace and attributes. I should also note that while MSTest v3 supports .NET Framework 4.6.2+, updating to a modern .NET target would be ideal, though I won't require it if there are constraints.\n\nNow I'm updating the project file with these changes.","outputTokens":886,"requestId":"BD0C:C42E6:20A222E:24F185E:6A07D8CE"},"id":"700b0f3b-4e0e-4674-9795-44f634151880","timestamp":"2026-05-16T02:39:27.773Z","parentId":"06fc2281-11d8-4964-abee-34dd1306878b"}
